<td><br>
<p>Requires training of existing staff or a qualified acupuncturist</p>
</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><br>
<p>Lack of side effects:</p>
<br>
<p>Side effects of acupuncture are mild, transient and self-limiting (<span=
 class=3D"tooltipsall classtoolTips16" style=3D"border-bottom:2px dotted #8=
88;">Lee et al., 2015</span>). There is no risk of drug-induced adverse eff=
ects (Streitberger and Kranke, 2011)</p>
</td>
<td>&nbsp;</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><br>
<p>Economical:</p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"mso-fareast-language: EN-AU; mso-no-p=
roof: yes;">PC6 acupoint stimulation is equivalent in effectiveness to comm=
only used antiemetics (ondansetron, dexamethasone, metoclopramide, cyclizin=
e, droperidol, prochlorperazine: 19 trials, 1708 participants) for nausea, =
vomiting and the need for rescue antiemetics.</span></p>
