_tta-shape-rounded vc_tta-o-shape-group vc_tta-controls-align-left"><div cl=
ass=3D"vc_tta-panels-container"><div class=3D"vc_tta-panels"><div class=3D"=
vc_tta-panel vc_active" id=3D"1558027935125-af726a24-0670" data-vc-content=
=3D".vc_tta-panel-body"><div class=3D"vc_tta-panel-heading"><h4 class=3D"vc=
_tta-panel-title vc_tta-controls-icon-position-left"><a href=3D"https://pop=
a4ease.com/site/index.php/exploration/#1558027935125-af726a24-0670" data-vc=
-accordion=3D"" data-vc-container=3D".vc_tta-container"><i class=3D"vc_tta-=
icon fa fa-check-square"></i><span class=3D"vc_tta-title-text">Results of a=
 USA Survey</span><i class=3D"vc_tta-controls-icon vc_tta-controls-icon-plu=
s"></i></a></h4></div><div class=3D"vc_tta-panel-body">
	<div class=3D"wpb_text_column wpb_content_element ">
		<div class=3D"wpb_wrapper">
			<p>A recent survey from the USA examined the perception of acupuncture a=
nd acupressure of 1,728 anaesthesia staff in 96 anaesthesiology departments=
 (Faircloth, 2014). Of the 292 respondents (17% response rate), 54% were an=
aesthesiologists, 44% nurses and 2% anaesthesia aiders. Although only 27% o=
f those surveyed had used acupuncture or acupressure with positive outcomes=
, 54% of the respondents said they would consider using acupuncture or acup=
ressure. Moreover, 74% of those surveyed would consider having acupuncture =
or acupressure education. The main barriers to implementing this therapy we=
re =E2=80=9Clack of scientific evidence=E2=80=9D (79%), including mechanism=
s and results of clinical trials in humans, =E2=80=9Cunavailability of cred=
entialed providers=E2=80=9D (71%), and =E2=80=9Clack of equipment=E2=80=9D =
(49%). Only 38% considered acupuncture as being too time consuming to perfo=
rm.</p>

		</div>
	</div>
</div></div><div class=3D"vc_tta-panel" id=3D"1558027935127-db796eef-3d62" =
data-vc-content=3D".vc_tta-panel-body"><div class=3D"vc_tta-panel-heading">=
<h4 class=3D"vc_tta-panel-title vc_tta-controls-icon-position-left"><a href=
=3D"https://popa4ease.com/site/index.php/exploration/#1558027935127-db796ee=
f-3d62" data-vc-accordion=3D"" data-vc-container=3D".vc_tta-container"><i c=
lass=3D"vc_tta-icon fa fa-users"></i><span class=3D"vc_tta-title-text">Resu=
lts of a survey of doctors, nurses, mid-wife and obstetricians in an Austra=
lian hospital</span><i class=3D"vc_tta-controls-icon vc_tta-controls-icon-p=
lus"></i></a></h4></div><div class=3D"vc_tta-panel-body">
	<div class=3D"wpb_text_column wpb_content_element ">
		<div class=3D"wpb_wrapper">
			<p>42% of 165 respondents believed acupuncture / acupressure was effecti=
ve for PONV. After being told this non-drug therapy was effective for PONV,=
 81% would encourage patients to use acupuncture / acupressure for PONV if =
it was offered at the hospital, and 88% wanted to have further education ab=
out this form of therapy.&nbsp; For further information, please <a href=3D"=
http://popa4ease.com/site/index.php/contact-us/">contact</a> the administra=
tor of this website.</p>

		</div>
	</div>
</div></div><div class=3D"vc_tta-panel" id=3D"1558028274435-edc6caef-9cb6" =
data-vc-content=3D".vc_tta-panel-body"><div class=3D"vc_tta-panel-heading">=
<h4 class=3D"vc_tta-panel-title vc_tta-controls-icon-position-left"><a href=
=3D"https://popa4ease.com/site/index.php/exploration/#1558028274435-edc6cae=
f-9cb6" data-vc-accordion=3D"" data-vc-container=3D".vc_tta-container"><i c=
lass=3D"vc_tta-icon fa fa-thumbs-o-up"></i><span class=3D"vc_tta-title-text=
">Acceptance of acupuncture by Australian doctors</span><i class=3D"vc_tta-=
controls-icon vc_tta-controls-icon-plus"></i></a></h4></div><div class=3D"v=
c_tta-panel-body">
	<div class=3D"wpb_text_column wpb_content_element ">
		<div class=3D"wpb_wrapper">
			<p>Although no such a survey has been conducted in Australia nationally,=
 it is likely that similar themes will be seen here. In Australia, acupunct=
ure is well-accepted by general practitioners. A national survey of 544 gen=
eral practitioners found that about 85% considered acupuncture to be effect=
ive and safe for primary care (<span class=3D"tooltipsall classtoolTips11" =
style=3D"border-bottom:2px dotted #888;" data-hasqtip=3D"3">Cohen et al., 2=
005</span>).&nbsp; 80% of GPs have referred their patients to have acupunct=
ure (<span class=3D"tooltipsall classtoolTips7" style=3D"border-bottom:2px =
dotted #888;" data-hasqtip=3D"0">Wardle et al., 2013</span>). &nbsp;Some me=
dical schools in Australia teach acupuncture as an elective course. That ac=
upuncture is not foreign to Australia medical staff provides a strong basis=
 for implementing and integrating acupuncture into the healthcare system.</=
p>

		</div>
	</div>
</div></div></div></div></div></div><section class=3D"vc_cta3-container">
	<div class=3D"vc_general vc_cta3 vc_cta3-style-3d vc_cta3-shape-rounded vc=
_cta3-align-left vc_cta3-color-classic vc_cta3-icon-size-md">
						<div class=3D"vc_cta3_content-container">
