				<header class=3D"vc_cta3-content-header">
					<h2>Assessment of Readiness for Change</h2>									</header>
				<p><img class=3D"size-medium wp-image-3595 alignright" src=3D"http://po=
pa4ease.com/site/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/checklist-300x200.jpg" alt=3D""=
 width=3D"300" height=3D"200"></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>The Checklist to Assess Organization Readiness (CARI) (<span class=3D"to=
oltipsall classtoolTips19" style=3D"border-bottom:2px dotted #888;" data-ha=
sqtip=3D"4">Barwick, 2011</span>) assesses the readiness of the system, sup=
port from the senior leadership, staff capability, the maturity of the impl=
ementation plan and training needed for implantation. The total score for t=
his modified CARI will be 100 points. &nbsp;A CARI total score of 80 points=
, with each category at least 15 points, will be considered to show that th=
e organisation is ready for implementation.<a name=3D"change"></a></p>
<a href=3D"http://popa4ease.com/site/index.php/modified-cari-readiness-chec=
klist/" class=3D"large otw-aqua radius otw-button"><i class=3D"general foun=
